HEADWORD: Prochordal
<hw>Pro*chor"dal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>pro +
chordal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated in front of the
notochord; -- applied especially to parts of the cartilaginous rudiments
in the base of the skull.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

